# 1. basic rules

- refer to issue number
  - issue number in current branch name
    - ex1) branch name: `feature/issue-32/test-issue`  
       => issue number: 32
    - ex2) branch name: `bug/issue-40/test-issue2`  
       => issue number: 40
  - in some case, it needs to refer Sub-issue of it
- Before Pull Request on GitHub, PR Content pre-check required
  - don't self PR upload without approval(Important)

# 2. basic PR Description(template)

```md
## 이슈번호

- {issue number}

## Description

// description of the issue
// Import the "description" part of the linked issue as it is.

- {changes}
```

# 3. Pull Request Rules(to dev)

## Merge Dir

- `{issue branch}` -> `{devlop branch}`
  - ex)
    - `feature/issue-31/test-issue` -> `dev-v1.2.0`
    - `bug/issue-32/test-issue` -> `dev-v1.2.0`
    - `docs/issue-33/test-issue` -> `dev-v1.2.0`

## title

- `{Same as the title of the issue}`
  - ex) title of issue: `[FEAT] Test Issue title (v1.2.0)`  
     => title of PR: `[FEAT] Test Issue title (v1.2.0)`

# 4. Pull Request Rules(from child issue to parent issue)

## Merge Dir

- `{Child issue branch}` -> `{Parent issue branch}`
  - ex)
    - `docs/issue-31/child-test-issue` -> `docs/issue-30/parent-test-issue`
    - `feature/issue-31/child-test-issue` -> `feature/issue-30/parent-test-issue`
    - `bug/issue-31/child-test-issue` -> `bug/issue-30/parent-test-issue`
    - `docs/issue-31/child-test-issue` -> `feature/issue-30/parent-test-issue`
    - `docs/issue-31/child-test-issue` -> `bug/issue-30/parent-test-issue`
    - `feature/issue-31/child-test-issue` -> `docs/issue-30/parent-test-issue`
    - `feature/issue-31/child-test-issue` -> `bug/issue-30/parent-test-issue`
    - `bug/issue-31/child-test-issue` -> `docs/issue-30/parent-test-issue`
    - `bug/issue-31/child-test-issue` -> `feature/issue-30/parent-test-issue`

## Title

- title: `{Same as the title of the issue}`
  - ex) title of issue: `[FEAT] Test Issue title (v1.2.0)`  
     => title of PR: `[FEAT] Test Issue title (v1.2.0)`

# 5. Pull Request Rules(to master)

## Merge Dir

- `{dev branch}` -> `master`
  - ex)
    - `dev-v1.2.0` -> `master`
    - `dev-v1.3.0` -> `master`

- refer to current branch

## Title

- title: `Merge of v{target version}`
  - ex: current branch name: `dev-v1.2.0`  
    => title: `Merge of v1.2.0`

## description

```md
## Changes(issue)

// Bring up all the titles of the issues associated with the branch.
// target version: at the end of title of issue.

- {changes}
```
